The paper discusses the performance of network coding, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of structured encoding matrices and the proposed methodology for computing optimal coding rates suggest a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the discussion of realistic scenarios and 5G networks suggests a potential focus on social and information networks (cs.SI).
